      "writtenOn": "2025-12-17T07:38:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi Ed\n\nI remember we have already discussed on this topic sometime back over discord,\nLLDP is neighbor discovery protocol, The network neighbor represents a piece of hardware. since SPDM is trying to identify TCP endpoints devices, it needs to probe LLDP interfaces",
      "parentUuid": "e6d113cc_0bad4d6f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 13,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 13,
        "endChar": 132
      },
      "revId": "59e967528a781ca4e1dd19552294f88370e3a6db",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
